# CSS Display Property

The display property determines how an HTML element is rendered on a webpage.

## Common Display Values

### Block

Takes full width available.

```css
div {
    display: block;
}
```

### Inline

Only takes required width.

```css
span {
    display: inline;
}
```

### Inline-Block

Behaves like inline but allows width and height.

```css
button {
    display: inline-block;
}
```

### None

Hides the element.

```css
.menu {
    display: none;
}
```

## Real-World Example

Navigation menus often use display properties to control layouts.

## Summary

Display controls how elements appear and interact with surrounding content.
